data.description: Relaxed country living located in the small community of Cowlington, OK, 3 miles west of Highway 59, sets a Cozy 2 bed 1 bath home/cabin setting on 2 acres m/l with two storage sheds. There is an optional 3rd bedroom with exterior access from the carport. This property has plenty of room for expansion for your hobby farm and garden or has enough room to put other cabins on the property. Paved roads to the driveway. One of the awesome features about this property is you have access to Cowlington Point Campgrounds and Boat Ramps as well as Short Mountain Campgrounds and Boat Ramp which is on Robert S. Kerr Lake on the Arkansas River. This lake is noted for its outstanding bass, crappie and catfishing and the lake is also suited for recreational boating and personal watercraft. This property is within 30 minutes of Sequoyah Wildlife Refuge, which is one of the most sought-after waterfowl destinations in the U.S. This house within 1 hour driving radius of Eufaula Lake which is the 10th largest manmade lake in the U.S. as well as Tenkiller Lake and Fort Gibson Lake. As far as convenience for all your personal needs it’s a short drive to Sallisaw, OK which has shopping, dining and hospital. For easy travel, access to the I-40/Hwy 59 intersection and a private airport makes this a convenient town to travel to and from. Fort Smith, AR is only 45 minutes away with 2 major hospitals, regional airport and all of the necessities that you would need.
